Troubleshooting Common Issues
Issue 1: Permission Denied Errors
Problem: Cannot create users or groups Solution: Ensure you're using sudo with administrative commands

sudo useradd username
Issue 2: User Already Exists
Problem: useradd reports user already exists Solution: Check existing users and use different username

grep username /etc/passwd
Issue 3: Cannot Delete Group
Problem: groupdel fails because group is in use Solution: Remove users from group first or change their primary group

sudo usermod -g users username
sudo groupdel groupname
Issue 4: Home Directory Not Created
Problem: User created but no home directory Solution: Use -m flag with useradd or create manually

sudo useradd -m username
# or
sudo mkdir /home/username
sudo chown username:username /home/username
